📌 ADMIN DASHBOARD — ASSIGNMENTS SECTION
Execution Instance Engine Specification v2.0

0️⃣ CORE PRINCIPLE
Assignment = Timestamped Execution Instance of a Test Template.
Assignment does NOT modify template.
Assignment creates:
Run
 └── Sessions (per student)
      └── Attempt data
Each assignment generates a unique:
runId
Even if same template reused.

1️⃣ NAVIGATION STRUCTURE
Assignments
   ├── Create Assignment
   ├── Assignment List
   ├── Live Monitor
   ├── Assignment History
   └── Bulk Operations

2️⃣ CREATE ASSIGNMENT FLOW
Creates:
institutes/{id}/academicYears/{year}/runs/{runId}
Initial state:
status = scheduled

STEP 1 — Select Test Template
Dropdown displays:
    • Template Name
    • Exam Type
    • Difficulty Distribution
    • Allowed Modes
    • Canonical ID (hidden)
    • Last Used
Template must be:
status ∈ {ready, assigned}
Cannot assign draft.

STEP 2 — Select Mode (Layer-Aware)
Mode selection is execution behavior selector.
Layer
Modes
L0
Operational
L1
Operational / Diagnostic
L2
Operational / Diagnostic / Controlled / Hard
L3
Same as L2
Mode selection locks:
    • Phase engine activation
    • Timing enforcement
    • Alert engine configuration
    • Min/Max enforcement
    • Revisit rules
    • Early submit policy
Store in run snapshot:
modeSnapshot
Cannot change after activation.

STEP 3 — Select Recipients
Options:
    • Entire batch
    • Multiple batches
    • Individual students
    • Filter by:
        ◦ Risk State (L2+)
        ◦ Discipline Index Range (L2+)
        ◦ Avg Raw % range
        ◦ Avg Accuracy % range
        ◦ Performance percentile (optional)
Important:
Only students with:
status == active
are eligible.
Recipient list stored explicitly:
recipientStudentIds[]
Never dynamically computed after creation.

STEP 4 — Time Window
Fields:
    • startWindow
    • endWindow
    • timezone
Optional:
    • attemptLimit (default = 1)
    • gracePeriod (minutes)
    • Shuffle Question Order (boolean)
Shuffle logic:
Only changes display order.
Does NOT change canonical structure.

STEP 5 — Confirmation Screen
Displays snapshot:
    • Template name
    • Mode
    • Phase config snapshot
    • Timing profile snapshot
    • Recipient count
    • Window
    • Academic year
    • Shuffle status
After confirm:
status = scheduled
Immutable fields from this point:
    • testId
    • modeSnapshot
    • phaseConfigSnapshot
    • timingProfileSnapshot
    • canonicalId
    • academicYear

3️⃣ ASSIGNMENT STATE MACHINE
scheduled → active → collecting → completed → archived
                    ↓
                cancelled
                    ↓
                terminated

scheduled
Window in future.
Editable:
    • Start time
    • End time
    • Recipients (before activation only)

active
Current time within window.
Sessions may start.
No structural edits allowed.

collecting
Some sessions still ongoing (window expired but grace active).

completed
All sessions ended.
Analytics finalized.
Immutable.

archived
Visibility only change.
No data mutation.

cancelled
Before activation.
No sessions allowed.

terminated
Manually stopped during active.
All open sessions force submitted.

